## GRID SYSTEM & RESPONSIVE CLASSES

### ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Syntaxe spécifique du template
Le template Lexend utilise une **syntaxe avec deux-points** pour les breakpoints responsive (comme UIKit), **PAS la syntaxe Bootstrap standard**.

### Grid/Colonnes - Syntaxe CORRECTE
```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Utiliser deux-points (:)
<div className="row child-cols g-4">
  <div className="col-12 lg:col-6 xl:col-4">...</div>
  <div className="col-12 lg:col-3">...</div>
  <div className="col-12 md:col-6 lg:col-4">...</div>
</div>

// ❌ INCORRECT - Ne PAS utiliser la syntaxe Bootstrap standard
<div className="row g-4">
  <div className="col-12 col-lg-6 col-xl-4">...</div>  // ❌ Ne fonctionne pas !
  <div className="col-12 col-lg-3">...</div>           // ❌ Ne fonctionne pas !
</div>
```

### Breakpoints disponibles
- `sm:` - Small (≥576px)
- `md:` - Medium (≥768px)
- `lg:` - Large (≥992px)
- `xl:` - Extra Large (≥1200px)

Remember: This is a B2B SaaS platform targeting French professionals. Every design and content decision should reflect professionalism, technical competence, and French business values. Always use Bootstrap 5 + UIKit CSS conventions, never Tailwind. The design is now standardized with clean, épuré aesthetics and consistent section headers using the hero-badge pattern.